Subject: How to photograph a supermassive black hole.
Description: The open source project to photograph a super-massive black hole took years of preparation, 8 satellites collecting data, 5 petabytes of data to analyze, and a community of brilliant collaborative minds. Join me to hear the story of how data scientists built a photograph of an object that can't be seen.  Speakers include:Norm Witte - Track: Science  - Duration: 1 hour
